Attempts to telephone from the station proved futile: the line remainedbusy, and I am not one to persevere in a struggle with faulty abstractionsof space. But my afternoon was poisoned, and the afternoon is my favoriteitem of time. I had been coaxing myself into believing, at the start of mylong journey, that I felt fairly fit; by now I felt terrible. The day wasunseasonably dull and damp. Palm trees are all right only in mi